content: An excellent app. I tried it. It integrated with my daily life really well. bought it.

Ive spoke to the developer about getting autosync to work through tasker and drive sync or the like and wass told without root on both devices its not possible. I love this app and wisah it got updated. Id be happy to plunk down some money for a black and white widget and autosync. Otherwise its perfect.

Works for exactly what I want it for. I hate going through menus and typing out my schedule, this app allows me to quickly jot down my schedule, meetings etc... by quickly writing it down. I also like being able to differentiate what type of event im attending by color coding. Needs an update as this is an older version. Also needs to include auto sync, ability to add attachments (jpg or pdf to an entry) and dark mode! Then it would be perfect.
Love this app....simple but effective
Very good application.
Very good but need sync for multiple devices.
I love handwriting notes.
Great handwriting calendar, easy to arrange note each day
Need to be able to add picture attachments
Plz add the option of attaching images.
Excellent app. It serves me very well for what I need.
Could be better and cleaner but best way to organize my work. Shocked no one else provides this.

SO GLAD I purchased this app. Normally don't purchase, but on Note 8 the note taking feature is EXCEPTIONAL and being able to quickly jot down my daily tasks and reminders is highly productive.  5 stars if you add different font thickness and color next time.  Buy it.
replyContent: If you are talking about graphic notes, you can tap the Pen icon to open Pen Settings.

content: Great for taking notes and keeping track of week done.  Only thing I would like to see is capability to attach photos to the notes.
Very nice app, but please give ma a landscape option...
love this! only wish I was able to sync with other people.
REALLY needs a copy/paste or repeating functionality, it's very annoying to have to write out every single day manually

It's a very easy to use daily planner,  writing, time slot and notes are very easy.  The 3 day week view is great. But, I still use another digital organizer to keep track of everything, just so I can search for specific things. The only thing that I don't like, is that you can't share your handwriting to other apps, but a very good app.  Cheers, Rocky
Tried the free version and was immediately impressed, Purchased full version the next day! Recommend this app - extremely useful!

Amazing! Love it! Especially week-view, where you can see all tasks and notes(handwritten). It would be great also to have the option of the same view in a month-page ( I mean the handwritten notes). Before purchasing, had some questions to the developers and their response was immediate(thanks to you guys). Woud recommend this app.
Please make so improvement!
Great App. Hope to add Year view and icons feature
Beautiful

I don't normally review stuff but this app is just too wonderful not to. A simple, straightforward, no-frills organizer with handwritten note support. Great and easy to use, well designed, and has all the features I needed. Thank you!
Best calendar note

This is the only app that keeps me organized. It's customizable, color coded, and you can organize your notes with a time or date or without. When I first downloaded this, I noticed a glitch and contacted developer. Got right back to me, fixed it, and followed up. Awesome!

At last a proper hand writing filofax!  Been looking for one of these for ages. The developer is genuinely interested in feedback. According to him,   because of the nature of the hand written notes, they are classed as images so at the moment, this doesn't sync with google. But I liked it so much I put all my stuff in it manually.  There's a note feature that I use all the time. It's worth downloading just for that!
Great app but needs landscape mode!!

This is exactly what I was waiting for. I alway used a Franklin Planner and when I went digital,  I have been searching for an app like it. This app does exactly what I need for tracking meeting notes and to do's. All it needs now is a cut and paste option and the ability to change existing note color and pen style. GREAT JOB!

Update: Nice to see its still under development. Lots of options for notes, reminders, tag, task status, tag filter, sort, and what not. Widget could be better but is still very useful. Great for scribbling a quick note and making a reminder if you want. Smooth, feature packed, attention to detail shows. Bought it very quickly after trial. Would like to have sync across devices, widget per note or tag, and sync with Google or Exchange for the text fields, with the notes as an add on.  That would not only be 5 stars but a killer app for Note.

Tried quite a few note/reminder apps. from the ones that do this type of thing this is the best if you have a stylus or just a finger this is really good give it a try. The 5 stars are also because the developer is absolutely great at getting back to you QUICKLY (like the same day).I've never rated an app a 5 but this, for the app itself and the very helpful developer, definitely deserves a five. Personally I think it deserves a 10
Will there be any sync functionality added to this?
replyContent:
I hope so. But at this point I don't have any estimated date of when it will be implemented.

P.S. If you have a question, please use emails for better support. Google Play does not send any notification to the developer when a review is added or updated.

content: WIDGETS.  Needs widgets for not to open the app or had a heavy window occupying all the screen.

This is the app I have been looking for! Something that allows me to organize/plan my day with full S pen support for all notes! I click my note, write what I want, assign a time/day and it's saved in the calendar. I have gone through 5-6 other apps before this one. Kuddos to the Dev!  *Now you can backup to Google drive* this app is the best!
Great app I have been looking for a long time. Missing just an option to synchronize automatically across the devices.

I love the full s pen ability and the simplicity of this app all together. However, would there be a way to line the notes up with the times they belong to? As if it was being written right along side the time on the left.
replyContent: Could you please write to zmiter.freeman@gmail.com to discuss the feature you are asking about?
